HEADWORD: Semiditone
<hw>Sem`i*di"tone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>semi-</ets> + <ets>ditone</ets>: cf. It. <ets>semiditono</ets>. Cf.
<er>Hemiditone</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Mus.)</fld> <def>A lesser third,
having its terms as 6 to 5; a hemiditone.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

